<font color="#FF0000">THREE QUESTIONS...</font><br>
<tt>Mon May 19  0:02:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Once a day for the past 27 years I have asked myself three <br>
questions (sometimes more than once daily):<br><br>
Did you wake up in a rice paddy?<br><br>
Do you have to strain the shit out of your water?<br><br>
Is anybody shooting at you?<br><br>
This has helped me put a little perspective on my days.  <br>
Oh yes, got to teach a group of desert storm vets in '92 <br>
for whom the first two questions differ (slightly)...<br><br>
Did I wake up on a sand dune?<br><br>
Do I have to strain the mustard out of my air?<br><br>
TJ, 5th SFGA, MACSOG(CCN)  69-71<br>

